<s1 id=MMainWindow>Mailer Main Window

	<idx>main window<\idx>
	<idx>Mailbox window<sort>mailbox window<\idx>
	<idx>Message View<sort>message view<\idx>
	<idx>Attachment list<sort>attachment list<\idx>

The Mailer main window consists of the Mailbox window, the Message
Header List, the message view area , and optionally, the Attachment list.

<p>To see the callouts for this figure, either resize your Help Viewer
window or click the horizontal scroll bar.

<newline>&empty;

<figure nonumber entity=MainWindow>
<\figure>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref MMsgList>
<item> <xref MMailboxButton>
<item> <xref MHeader>
<item> <xref MAttach>
<item> <Xref MComposeWindow>
<\list>

<s2 id=MMsgList>Mailer Mailbox Window
<location id=dtmailViewmainWindowWork-AreapanedWform2MessageListSWMessageList>&empty;<\location>

	<idx>Mailbox window<sort>mailbox window<\idx>

The Mailbox window contains a menu bar, the headers of messages in your 
mailbox, and a row of buttons for common functions, called the Toolbar. 
You can scroll through the list of messages if it is longer than what is 
currently displayed. You can also use the sash to resize the list to 
display more or fewer messages than what is displayed. This is where 
new messages are displayed in your Inbox.

<p>To see the callouts for this figure, either resize your Help Viewer 
window or click the horizontal scroll bar.

<newline>&empty;

<figure nonumber entity=MessageHeaderList> 
<\figure>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref MMainWindow>
<item> <xref MMailboxButton>
<item> <xref MHeader>
<item> <xref MAttach>
<item> <xref MessageHeaderListOptions> 
<item> <xref ComposingMessagesTA>
<\list>

<s2 id=MMailboxButton>Mailer Toolbar Buttons

<location id=dtmailViewmainWindowWork-AreapanedWform2RowColumnDelete>&empty;<\location>
<location id=dtmailViewmainWindowWork-AreapanedWform2RowColumnNext>&empty;<\location>
<location id=dtmailViewmainWindowWork-AreapanedWform2RowColumnPrevious>&empty;<\location>
<location id=dtmailViewmainWindowWork-AreapanedWform2RowColumnReply>&empty;<\location>
<location id=dtmailViewmainWindowWork-AreapanedWform2RowColumnPrint>&empty;<\location>

	<idx>Mailbox buttons<sort>mailbox buttons<\idx>
	<idx>Toolbar buttons<sort>toolbar buttons<\idx>
	<idx>Delete button:on Mailbox window<sort>delete button:on mailbox window<\idx>
	<idx>Next button:on Mailbox window<sort>next button:on mailbox window<\idx>
	<idx>Previous button:on Mailbox window<sort>previous button:on mailbox window<\idx>
	<idx>Reply, Include Message button:on Mailbox window<sort>reply, include message button:on mailbox window<\idx>
	<idx>Forward button:on Mailbox window<sort>forward button:on mailbox window<\idx>
	<idx>New Message button:on Mailbox window<sort>new message button:on mailbox window<\idx>
	<idx>Print One button:on Mailbox window<sort>print one button:on mailbox window<\idx>
<!--<idx>Check for New Mail button:on Mailbox window<sort>check for new mail button:on mailbox window<\idx>-->
	<idx>toolbar<\idx>

<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=MButtons>
<\figure> 

The Toolbar contains buttons that offer an alternative to using the 
menus for common functions.

<lablist nowrap>
<labheads>\Button \ Function
\ Delete \	Deletes the selected messages from the mailbox. (There is an equivalent item in the Message menu.)

\ Next \	Displays the message that follows the currently selected one. 
		(There is an equivalent item in the View menu.)

\ Previous \	Displays the message that precedes the currently selected one. (There is an equivalent item in the View menu.)

\ Reply, Include Message \	Opens a Compose window with the email address of the recipient filled in, and the message body included.  (There is an 
equivalent item in the Compose menu.)

\ Forward \	Opens a Compose window with the text of the selected message 
and its attachments, if any, loaded.  (There is an equivalent item in the 
Compose menu.)

\ New Message \	Opens a Compose window.  (There is an equivalent item
in the Compose menu.) 

\ Print One \	Prints one copy of the selected messages. (There is an 
equivalent item in the Message menu.)

<!--\ Abbreviated Headers \  Displays the full or abbreviated headers for your
                         messages.  (There is an equivalent menu item in the 
                         View menu.) 
 
\ Check for New Mail \  Checks if any new messages have arrived.  (There is
                        an equivalent menu item in the Mailbox menu.)-->

<\lablist>

To change the appearance of these buttons, refer to <xref ToolbarOptions>.

