<\list>

<s1 id=MComposeWindow>Mailer Compose Window
<location id=dtmailComposeWindow>&empty;<\location>

	<idx>Compose window<sort>compose window<\idx>
<idx>Compose window buttons<sort>compose window buttons<\idx>
        <idx>Send button:on Compose window<sort>send button:on compose window<\idx>
        <idx>Save As button:on Compose window<sort>save as button:on compose
window<\idx>
        <idx>Close button:on Mailbox window<sort>close button:on compose window<\idx>
        <idx>sending messages<\idx>
        <idx>messages, sending<\idx>

Address, compose, and send your message using the Compose window.

<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=MCompWindow>
<\figure>

<term nogloss>To<\term> and <term nogloss>Cc<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Contain pulldown menus that list all the aliases you have created.
You can choose one or more aliases as recipients for your message.  Also 
contains an Aliases item that opens the <xref MailAliasOptions> from which you 
can create, delete, or change aliases.
<\list>
 
<term nogloss>Send<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Sends your message to the addressed destination (duplicates the Send
item on the File menu.) For information on sending mail, refer
to <xref ComposingMessagesTA>.
<\list>
 
<term nogloss>Save As<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Saves either both the headers and message body, or the message body only, as follows:
 
<lablist>
\ Draft Message\ Saves the headers and message body as a draft in a file that            you specify in the default mailbox <var>HomeDirectory<\var><computer>/MailDrafts<\computer>.
\ Template \ Opens the Templates dialog box, where you can specify a
            template name for the headers and message body in
            the default directory <var>HomeDirectory<\var><computer>/MailTemplates<\computer>.
\ Text \    Opens a File Selection dialog box, where you can specify the name 
            of the file to save the message body to.  If a
            file with the same name already exists, you can either
            overwrite it or append the message to it.  Mailer does not
            save the headers for this option.
<\lablist>
<\list>
 
<term nogloss>Close<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Quits the current Compose window (duplicates the Close item
on the File menu.)
<\list>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ComposingMessagesTA>
<item> <xref MMainWindow>
<\list>

