<s1 id=MMailboxMenu>Mailer Mailbox Menu
	<location id=dtmailViewmainWindowmenubarFile>&empty;<\location>

	<idx>Mailbox menu<sort>mailbox menu<\idx>
	<idx>Check for New Mail:on Mailbox menu<sort>check for new mail:on mailbox menu<\idx>
	<idx>Show Views:on Mailbox menu<sort>show views:on mailbox menu<\idx>
<!--
	<idx>Auto-Filing Mailboxes<sort>Auto-Filing Mailboxes:mailbox menu<\idx>
-->
	<idx>Select All Messages:on Mailbox menu<sort>select all messages:on mailbox menu<\idx>
	<idx>New Mailbox:on Mailbox menu<sort>new mailbox:on mailbox menu<\idx>
	<idx>Rename Mailbox:on Mailbox menu<sort>rename mailbox:on mailbox menu<\idx>
	<idx>Delete Mailbox:on Mailbox menu<sort>delete mailbox:on mailbox menu<\idx>
	<idx>Open Mailbox:on Mailbox menu<sort>open mailbox:on mailbox menu<\idx>
	<idx>Destroy Deleted Messages:on Mailbox menu<sort>destroy deleted messages:on mailbox menu<\idx>
	<idx>Close:on Mailbox menu<sort>close:on mailbox menu<\idx>

<p gentity=Mailer-Mailbox-Menu gposition=left>
<newline>&empty;

<term nogloss>Check for New Mail<\term> retrieves new messages awaiting 
delivery to your mailbox immediately, rather than waiting for the specified 
auto-retrieval time.<newline>

<!--
<term nogloss>Auto-Filing Mailboxes<\term> lists the mailboxes that
contain new messages.  This function is handy if you have set up automatic 
filing of incoming messages in mailboxes other than your Inbox.  For details,
see <xref FilingMessagesTA> and <xref NotificationOptions>.<newline> 
-->

<term nogloss>Show Views<\term> opens the <xref DTMAILHELPVIEWS>, where you can
create, edit, delete, or update view.

<term nogloss>Select All Messages<\term> selects all the messages that are in
the Message Header List.<newline> 

<term nogloss>New Mailbox<\term> opens and enables you to name a new mailbox.<newline>

<term nogloss>Rename Mailbox<\term> gives a new name of your choice to
a mailbox you specify.<newline>
 
<term nogloss>Delete Mailbox<\term> removes the mailbox you specify.<newline>

<term nogloss>Open Mailbox<\term> displays a submenu from which you can 
choose to open one of the following: the Inbox, the file that contains your
outgoing messages (Sent Mail), a File Selection dialog box with the default
mail directory displayed (Select Mailbox), one of the mailboxes in 
the default mail directory (Other Mailboxes), or one of the mailboxes that 
you opened, or moved or copied messages to previously in this Mailer session.
<newline>

<term nogloss>Destroy Deleted Messages<\term> permanently removes the messages 
from the deleted messages list.<newline>

<!--
<term nogloss>Mail Options<\term> opens the Mail Options dialog box through 
which you can change options in the following categories: Message Header List, 
Message View, Compose Window, Message Filing, Vacation Message, Templates, Aliases, 
and Advanced.<newline>
-->

<term nogloss>Close<\term> quits the current mailbox.

