<!--
<lablist width=2in>
<labheads>\Use \ To
\ Check for New Mail \	Retrieve any new messages awaiting delivery to your mailbox sooner 
			than the specified auto-retrieval time. See <xref MessageHeaderListOptions> 
			for more information on changing these settings.

\ Open Inbox \		Opens your Inbox when in mailboxes other than your Inbox.

\ New \ 		Open and enable you to name a new mailbox, separate from the one currently open.

\ Open \		Open other mailboxes.

\ Destroy Deleted Messages \ Permanently removes the messages from the deleted messages list.  
			You cannot get a message back once you have made this selection.

\Mail Options \		Opens the Mail Options dialog box through which you can change options in the 
			following categories: Message Header List, Message View, Compose Window, 
			Message Filing, Vacation, Templates, Aliases, and Advanced.

\Close \		Quit the current mailbox. 
<\lablist>		
-->

<s1 id=MMsgMenu>Mailer Message Menu
	<location id=dtmailViewmainWindowmenubarMessage>&empty;<\location>

	<idx>Message menu<sort>message menu<\idx>
	<idx>Open:on Message menu<sort>open:on message menu<\idx>
	<idx>Copy Selected Text:on Message menu<sort>copy selected text:on 
message menu<\idx>
	<idx>Select All Text:on Message menu<sort>select all text:on message 
menu<\idx>
	<idx>Save As Text:on Message menu<sort>save as text:on message menu<\idx>
	<idx>Attachments:on Message menu<sort>attachments:on message menu<\idx>
	<idx>Copy To Mailbox:on Message menu<sort>copy to mailbox:on message 
menu<\idx>
	<idx>Print One:on Message menu<sort>print one:on message menu<\idx>
	<idx>Print:on Message menu<sort>print:on message menu<\idx>
	<idx>Search:on Message menu<sort>search:on message menu<\idx>
	<idx>Delete:on Message menu<sort>delete:on message menu<\idx>
	<idx>Undelete Last:on Message menu<sort>undelete last:on message menu<\idx>
	<idx>Undelete From List:on Message menu<sort>undelete from list:on message 
menu<\idx>

<p gentity=Mailer-Message-Menu gposition=left>
<newline>&empty;

<term nogloss>Open<\term> opens the selected message in a separate window
(message view).<newline>

<term nogloss>Copy Selected Text<\term> copies the selected message text for
placement into a Compose window or other text document.<newline>

<term nogloss>Select All Text<\term> selects all the text in the 
message view area.<newline>

<term nogloss>Save As Text<\term> saves the selected message as a text file
with a designated name and location.   If a file with the same name already 
exists, you can either overwrite it or append the message to it.<newline>

<term nogloss>Attachments<\term> displays a submenu from which you
can choose to: save the selected attachment with a designated name and
location (Save As), select all the attachments (Select All), open the
selected attachment in a separate window (Open), or print the attachment
(Print).  The Open and Print items are not active if you cannot open or
print the selected attachment.
 
<p>When you choose Print from the Attachments menu, the Print dialog box 
opens, from which you can specify the printer, number of copies, banner 
page title, whether to print page numbers, and print command-line options.
 
<p>See also <xref OpenAttachmentsTA>, <xref SendingAttachmentsTA>,
<xref MovingAttachmentsTA>, and <xref AttachPrintTA>.

<term nogloss>Copy To Mailbox<\term> copies the selected messages to one
of the locations that you choose from from the submenu:<newline>

<lablist nowrap>
\ Inbox \ The mailbox where you receive email by default.
                                                           
\ Select Mailbox \ A mailbox that you specify from a File Selection
dialog box

\ Other Mailboxes \ One of the mailboxes in the default mail directory 
 
\ <var>previous mailboxes<\var> \  The mailboxes that you opened, or moved
or copied messages to previously in this Mailer session
<\lablist>
 
<note>
You can create a mailbox using the File Selection dialog box by choosing
Select Mailbox from the Copy To Mailbox submenu; however, once the mailbox
is created, it is not opened, and the selected message is automatically
copied to the new mailbox.  If you make an error while typing the name of the
mailbox, you may not discover it until you browse your mailboxes.
<\note>

<term nogloss>Print One<\term> prints one copy of the selected messages.
<newline>

<term nogloss>Print<\term> opens a dialog box where you can set print
settings, such as printer, number of copies, and so on.<newline>

<term nogloss>Search<\term> looks for a message by the sender, subject, or 
recipient.<newline>

<term nogloss>Delete<\term> removes selected messages from the mailbox.  
These messages are kept in the deleted messages list until you permanently 
delete them by choosing Destroy Deleted Messages from the Mailbox menu.
<newline>

<term nogloss>Undelete Last<\term> recovers the last deleted message and 
returns it to its original place in the mailbox.<newline>

<term nogloss>Undelete From List<\term> displays a list of deleted messages 
so you can select a message to recover and return to its original place 
in the mailbox.

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ReadAMessageTA>
<item> <xref SavingMessagesTA>
<item> <xref FindingMessagesTA>
<item> <xref PrintingMessagesTA>
<item> <xref DeleteAMessageTA>
<item> <xref UndeletingMessageTA>
<item> <xref MMailboxMenu>
<\list>

<!--
<lablist width=2in>
<labheads>\Use \ To
\ Open \	Open the selected message into a separate window. The Edit
and Attachments menus are available to you.

\ Save As Text \	Save and name the selected message with a designated name and location.

\ Copy To \	Copy the selected messages into another mailbox or your
Inbox.

\ Print \	Print a single selected message or multiple selected messages.
		A print dialog box appears through which you can: change the printer, 
		print multiple copies, give the banner page a title, print formatted 
		pages (page numbers), add your own print command options. 

\ Search \	Search for a message by the sender, subject, or recipient(s).
		You can find a single message or a group of messages. See 
		<xref FindAMessage> for more information.
 
\ Select All \  Select all the messages within the Message Header List of your mailbox.

\ Delete \	Remove selected messages from the mailbox. These messages are kept 
		in the deleted messages list until you permanently delete them by 
		choosing Destroy Deleted Messages from the Mailbox menu.

\ Undelete Last \ 	Undelete the last deleted message and return it to its original 
		place in your mailbox. 

\ Undelete From List \	Display a list of deleted messages so you can select a deleted 
		message to undelete and return to its original place in your mailbox. 
<\lablist>
-->
  
