<s1 id=MViewMenu>Mailer View Menu
    <location id=dtmailViewmainWindowmenubarView>&empty;<\location>
 
    <idx>View menu<sort>view menu<\idx>
    <idx>Next:on View menu<sort>next:on view menu<\idx>
    <idx>Previous:on View menu<sort>previous:on view menu<\idx>
    <idx>Abbreviated Headers:on View menu<sort>abbreviated headers:on view menu<\idx>
    <idx>Change Char Set:on View menu<sort>change char set:on view menu<\idx>
    <idx>By Date/Time:on View menu<sort>by date and time:on view menu<\idx>
    <idx>By Sender:on View menu<sort>by sender:on view menu<\idx>
    <idx>By Subject:on View menu<sort>by subject:on view menu<\idx>
    <idx>By Size:on View menu<sort>by size:on view menu<\idx>
    <idx>By Status:on View menu<sort>by status:on view menu<\idx>
 
<p gentity=Mailer-View-Menu gposition=left>
<newline>&empty;
<term nogloss>Next<\term> opens the message just after the current message.
<newline>
<term nogloss>Previous<\term> opens the message just before the current message.<newline>
<term nogloss>Abbreviated Headers<\term> controls the detail displayed in
message headers.<newline>
<term nogloss>Change Char Set<\term> converts the text of the selected 
message to the character set that you select, the name of which is 
displayed in the footer immediately below the Toolbar icons.  Continuously 
choosing this item cycles through the character set choices that are 
available (for example, ISO-2022-JP, EUC-JP, ISO-8859-1, and US-ASCII).  
The item named Default Char Set is the default encoding for your 
machine.<newline>
<term nogloss>By Date/Time<\term> sorts messages in the current mailbox by
the date and time they were received.<newline>
<term nogloss>By Sender<\term> sorts messages in the current mailbox
alphabetically by the sender of the message.<newline>
<term nogloss>By Subject<\term> sorts messages in the current mailbox by
grouping together all messages with the same subject.<newline>
<term nogloss>By Size<\term> sorts messages in the current mailbox by
increasing size.<newline>
<term nogloss>By Status<\term> sorts messages in the current mailbox by
the status of the message.
 
<procedure>See Also
