<p gentity=Mailer-Options-Menu gposition=left>
<newline>&empty;

<term nogloss>Basic<\term> opens the Mailer Basic Options dialog box, where
you can determine how often to check for new mail and save the mailbox,
whether to save outgoing mail, how many headers to display, whether to 
display message numbers, whether to permanently remove deleted
messages when you close the mailbox, as well as to specify your
IMAP Inbox server name.<newline>

<term nogloss>Aliases<\term> opens the Mailer Aliases Options dialog box, 
where you can add, change, or remove your own private distribution lists, 
known as aliases.<newline> 

<term nogloss>Compose Window<\term> opens the Mailer Compose Window Options 
dialog box, where you can define the format settings in the Compose 
window.<newline>

<!--
<term nogloss>Filing and Notification<\term> opens the Mailer Filing and  
Notification Options dialog box, where you can set up how you want to be
notified when new mail arrives, as well as the rules for automatically
filing the incoming messages that meet certain criteria, such as those 
from a certain sender, in the mailboxes that you specify.<newline>
-->

<term nogloss>Message View<\term> opens the Mailer Message View Options 
dialog box, where you can configure how messages appear in your mailbox.<newline>

<term nogloss>Move Menu Setup<\term> opens the Mailer Move Menu Setup Options 
dialog box, where you can specify the frequently used mailboxes that are
shown on the Open Mailbox submenu of the Mailbox menu and the Copy To 
Mailbox submenu of the Message menu, as well as the Move menu.  Here, you 
can also define the number of mailboxes that you recently opened that you
want shown on the Copy To Mailbox submenu and the Move menu.<newline>

<term nogloss>Notification<\term> opens the Mailer 
Notification Options dialog box, where you can set up how you want to be
notified when new mail arrives.<newline> 

<term nogloss>Signature<\term> opens the Mailer Signature Options dialog box, 
where you can create a signature for outgoing messages.<newline>

<term nogloss>Templates<\term> opens the Mailer Templates Options dialog box, 
where you can create your own template files that contain headers and text 
that you frequently use in composing messages.<newline>

<term nogloss>Toolbar<\term> opens the Mailer Toolbar Options dialog box, where
you can configure the appearance of the buttons in the Toolbar, either as 
icons or with text.<newline>

<term nogloss>Vacation Message<\term> opens the Mailer Vacation Message 
Options dialog box, where you can set the vacation notifier option to 
respond to incoming messages.<newline>

<term nogloss>Advanced<\term> opens the Mailer Advanced Options dialog box, 
where you can set some advanced mail defaults.<newline>

<p>The buttons in the dialog boxes work as follows:

<lablist>
\ OK \          Applies changes and closes the dialog box
\ Apply \       Changes the options you have edited
\ Reset \       Resets options to the way they were since you last applied them
\ Cancel \      Closes the dialog box without applying your changes
\ Help \        Displays help for the dialog box
<\lablist>

