<newline>&empty;

<term nogloss>Include<\term> includes a text file in your new message at the
insertion point.<newline>

<term nogloss>Save As<\term> saves both the headers and the message you 
are composing as a template or as a draft, or the message body only
as text, depending on what you choose from the submenu.  For details,
see <xref MComposeWindow>.<newline>

<term nogloss>Save Outgoing Mail<\term> places a copy of the message you are 
sending in the default mailbox <var>HomeDirectory<\var><computer>/Mail/sent.mail<\computer> or in a mailbox of your choice.  The message is saved as a 
text file with the headers intact.<newline>

<term nogloss>Send<\term> sends your message to the addressees and Cc recipients.<newline>

<term nogloss>Send As<\term> sends your message in Internet MIME format or 
Sun Mail Tool format. Internet MIME is the default. To turn off this default,
see the option, <link hyperlink=dtmailSendMailInMIME>Send mail in MIME format<\link>, in the <xref AdvancedMailOptions>.<newline>

