<s1 id=MComposeEditMenu>Mailer Compose Edit Menu
<location id=dtmailComposeWindowmenubarEdit>&empty;<\location>

	<idx>Compose window Edit menu<sort>compose window edit menu<\idx>
	<idx>Edit menu:on Compose window<sort>edit menu:on compose window<\idx>
	<idx>Undo:on Compose window Edit menu<sort>undo:on compose window edit menu<\idx>
	<idx>Cut:on Compose window Edit menu<sort>cut:on compose window edit menu<\idx>
	<idx>Copy:on Compose window Edit menu<sort>copy:on compose window edit menu<\idx>
	<idx>Paste:on Compose window Edit menu<sort>paste:on compose window edit menu<\idx>
	<idx>Paste Special:on Compose window Edit menu<sort>paste special:on compose window edit menu<\idx>
        <idx>Clear:on Compose window Edit menu<sort>clear:on compose window edit menu<\idx>
        <idx>Delete:on Compose window Edit menu<sort>delete:on compose window edit menu<\idx>
        <idx>Select All:on Compose window Edit menu<sort>select all:on compose window edit menu<\idx>
        <idx>Find/Change:on Compose window Edit menu<sort>find and changeclose:on compose window edit menu<\idx>
        <idx>Check Spelling:on Compose window Edit menu<sort>check spelling:on compose window edit menu<\idx>

<p gentity=Mailer-Compose-Edit-Menu gposition=left>
<newline>&empty;

<term nogloss>Undo<\term> reverses the last edit in the text area.
<newline>
<term nogloss>Cut<\term> removes the selected text and stores it on the
clipboard.  Only one selection can be stored on the clipboard at a time. If
text is already there, the most current selection overwrites it.<newline>
<term nogloss>Copy<\term> stores a copy of the selected text on the clipboard.
<newline>
<term nogloss>Paste<\term> inserts the contents of the clipboard at the
insertion point.<newline>
<term nogloss>Paste Special<\term> inserts the contents of the clipboard at
the insertion point surrounded above and below by Begin and End Included
Message (Bracketed), or indented markers (Indented).<newline>
<term nogloss>Clear<\term> removes the selection and leaves the resulting white
space.<newline>
<term nogloss>Delete<\term> removes the selection and the resulting white space.
<newline>
<term nogloss>Select All<\term> selects all the text in the text area.<newline>
<term nogloss>Find/Change<\term> opens a dialog box where you can search 
for words or phrases in your message and make changes to occurrences that are 
found.<newline>
<term nogloss>Check Spelling<\term> runs the spelling checker on your mail message 
and displays a dialog box that shows the words that might be spelled 
incorrectly, one by one, as well as providing suggestions for the correct 
spellings. You can change one or all instances of a word.

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref FindTextTA>
<item> <xref SpellCheckTA>
<item> <xref EditExistingTA>
<\list>

<!--
<lablist width=2in>
<labheads> \Use \ To
\ Undo \	Reverse the last editing action in the text area.

\ Cut \		Remove the selected text and store it on the clipboard. 
		Only one selection can be stored on the clipboard at a time. 
		If text is already there, the most current selection 
		overwrites it.	

\ Copy \	Store a copy of the selected text on the clipboard. Only 
		one selection can be stored at a time.  If text is already 
		there, the most current selection overwrites it.

\ Paste \	Insert the contents of the clipboard at the insertion point.

\ Paste Special \	Insert the contents of the clipboard at the insertion 
		point and surrounded above and below by Begin and End Included 
		Message, or indented markers.  

\ Clear \	Remove the selection and leave the resulting white space.

\ Delete \	Remove the selection and the resulting white space. 

\ Select All \	Select all the text in the text area.

\ Find/Change \	Open a dialog box that enables you to search for words or phrases 
		in your message and make changes to occurrences that are found.

<p indent gentity=Generic-Mouse-Click ghyperlink=survival-skills-mouse glinktype=Definition>

\ Check Spelling \ Run the spell checker on your mail message and display a dialog 
		box that lists words that might be spelled incorrectly. You can Find, 
		Change, or Change All instances of a word.
<\lablist>
-->

<s1 id=MComposeAttachMenu>Mailer Compose Attachments Menu
<location id=dtmailComposeWindowmenubarAttach>&empty;<\location>

	<idx>Compose window Attachments menu<sort>compose window attachments menu<\idx>
	<idx>Attachments menu:on Compose window<sort>attachments menu:on compose window<\idx>
