message.<newline>
<term nogloss>Save As<\term> saves, or saves and renames, the selected attachment as a file.<newline>
<term nogloss>Delete<\term> removes selected attachments from the list.<newline>
<term nogloss>Undelete<\term> restores deleted attachments to the list, one by one.
<newline>
<term nogloss>Rename<\term> opens a dialog box in which you can rename 
the selected attachment.<newline>
<term nogloss>Select All<\term> selects all the attachments in the list.
<newline>
<term nogloss>Show List<\term> shows or hides the Attachment list. You can only
hide the list if no attachments are in it.<newline>
<term nogloss>Open<\term> opens the attachment.<newline>
<term nogloss>Print<\term> displays a dialog box in which you can choose
printer options for the selected attachment.

<note>Depending on the type of attachment you have selected, the last item 
on this menu varies.  Besides Print, it could be Open, Compose, and so on. 
<\note>

