<s1 id=DTMAILHELPLOGIN>Mailer Login Dialog Box

    <idx>Login dialog box, reference<sort>login dialog box, reference<\idx>
    <idx>IMAP Server, in Mailer Login dialog box<sort>IMAP server, in mailer login dialog box<\idx>
    <idx>Login, in Mailer Login dialog box<sort>login, in mailer login dialog box<\idx>
    <idx>Password, in Mailer Login dialog box<sort>password, in mailer login dialog box<\idx>
    <idx>Retrieve attachments, in Mailer Login dialog box<sort>retrieve attachments, in mailer login dialog box<\idx>
    <idx>Always, in Mailer Login dialog box<sort>always, in mailer login dialog box<\idx>
    <idx>When Open, in Mailer Login dialog box<sort>when open, in mailer login dialog box<\idx>


<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=Mailer-Login>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;

<term nogloss>IMAP Server<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>The name of the IMAP server to which you are logging in
<\list>

<term nogloss>Login<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>The name that you use to log in to your IMAP mail server
<\list>

<term nogloss>Password<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>The password that is associated with your login name
<\list>

<term nogloss>Retrieve attachments<\term>
<p>Use these options to determine whether to have Mailer load attachment
contents when it loads messages.  For example, if you Inbox takes a long
time to load, then you may opt to have Mailer load the attachment contents
only when you want to read them.<\p>

<term nogloss>Always<\term><newline>
<list plain tight>
<item>When you click a message header, Mailer loads the message text and
attachment contents.  This is the default option.
<\list>

<term nogloss>When Open<\term><newline>
<list plain tight>
<item>When you click a message header, Mailer loads the message text but
not the attachment contents.  They are loaded only when you double-click
the attachment icon.
<\list>
 
<lablist>
\ Login \ Logs into the IMAP server.
 
\ Cancel \ Cancels the login operation and opens the File Selection 
Dialog Box, where you can specify a local mailbox to open on your desktop. 
<\lablist>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref LoginMBTA>
<\list>


<s1 id=MessageHeaderListOptions>Mailer Basic Options Dialog Box
<location id=dtmailMailboxOptionsMessageHeaderList>&empty;<\location>

	<idx>Mailer Basic Options dialog box, reference<sort>mailer basic options dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Check for new mail every, in Mailer Basic Options dialog box<sort>check for new mail every, in mailer basic options dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Save mailbox every, in Mailer Basic Options dialog box<sort>save mailbox every, in mailer basic options dialog box<\idx>
