Choose Basic from the Options menu to determine how often to check for new mail
and save the mailbox, whether to save outgoing mail, how many headers 
to display, whether to display message numbers, whether to permanently
remove deleted messages when you close the mailbox, as well as to specify your
IMAP Inbox server name.

<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=Mailer-Message-Header-List>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;

<term nogloss>Mailbox Updates:<\term><newline> 
<term nogloss>Check for new mail every nn Seconds<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item> This setting determines how often Mailer checks for new mail. 
You can increase or decrease the default value of 300 seconds, 
or five minutes.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Save mailbox every nn Minutes<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item> This setting determines how often Mailer saves the mailbox. 
You can increase or decrease the default value of 30 minutes. 
<\list>

<!--
<term nogloss>Update mailbox when idle for nn Seconds<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item> This setting determines how often Mailer saves the mailbox. 
You can increase or decrease the default value of 30 seconds.  When
this option is selected, Mailer does not check for new messages or
save the mailbox.  You may want to turn on this option while composing
a message, for example. 
<\list>
-->

<term nogloss>Save a copy of outgoing mail in:<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Selecting this option means that all mail messages that you saved
are automatically saved in the file shown in the text field. The default 
is <var>HomeDirectory<\var><computer>/Mail/sent.mail<\computer>.  You can turn this option off for an individual message by deselecting Save Outgoing Mail from 
the Compose File menu.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Display nn headers<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item>This setting determines how many headers are displayed 
in your message view area.  The number of headers displayed offsets the
message view area size.  Displaying more headers means a smaller message
view area; displaying less headers means a larger one.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Show To: recipient when mail is from me<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item> If this option is selected, the headers of your outgoing messages 
display the recipients of the messages instead of your mail address.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Display message numbers<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item> If this option is selected, the message number is shown 
to the left of each message in your Message Header List.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Destroy Deleted Messages:<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>If the <quote>When I close the mailbox<\quote> option is selected, 
Mailer destroys the deleted messages when you close the mailbox.  
<item>If the <quote>Show confirmation notice<\quote> option is selected, 
Mailer posts a notice when you close the mailbox that asks you if you 
want to destroy deleted messages.
<\list>

<term nogloss>IMAP Inbox Server<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>The server name displayed in this field is the name that you typed
in the IMAP Server field in the <xref DTMAILHELPLOGIN> when
you first logged in to IMAP.

If you change this server name and click Apply or OK, next time you
log in to IMAP, Mailer displays the new name in the <xref DTMAILHELPLOGIN>. 
<\list>

