<term nogloss>Frequently used mailboxes to show on Move menu:<\term><newline>
<term nogloss>Local<\term><newline>
<list plain tight>
<item>Select this option to indicate that your frequently used mailboxes are
on the local server.
<\list>

<term nogloss>IMAP Server<\term><newline>
<list plain tight>
<item>Select this option to indicate that your frequently used mailboxes are
on the IMAP server.  Also, type the server name in the text field.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Path/Mailbox Name:<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Type a path and file name for a mailbox and click Add to include it
in the list.
<\list>
 
<lablist>
\ Select \  Opens a File Selection dialog box where you can specify the
            path and file name
\ Add \  Adds the path and file name in the Path/Mailbox Name field
         to the list
\ Delete \  Removes the selected file name from the list
\ Change \  Changes the selected file name to the information
            indicated in the Path/Mailbox Name field
\ Alphabetize \  Arranges the list in alphabetical order
\ Move Up \ Moves the selected Path/Mailbox Name toward the beginning
            of the list
\ Move Down \ Moves the selected Path/Mailbox Name toward the end 
            of the list
<\lablist>
 
<term nogloss>Display up to: nn Recently visited mailboxes<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Specifies how many recently visited mailboxes Mailer displays.  The
default is up to ten mailboxes.  You can increase or decrease this number.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Default Mailbox Folder<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Specifies the path where Mailer looks for your mailboxes.
The default is <var>HomeDirectory<\var><computer>/Mail<\computer>.
<\list>
 
<term nogloss>IMAP Filing Server<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Specifies the name of the IMAP server where Mailer looks for your 
default mailbox directory.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Default IMAP Folder<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Specifies the path in the IMAP server where Mailer looks for your 
mailboxes.  The default is <var>HomeDirectory<\var><computer>/Mail<\computer>.
<\list>

