Choose Notification from the Options menu to set up how
you want to be notified when new mail arrives.

<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=Mailer-Filing-Notify>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;

<term nogloss>General Mailbox Notification:<\term><newline>
<term nogloss>Signal new mail with:<\term>

<list plain tight>
<item> These settings determine how Mailer signals new incoming mail.

<lablist>
\ <term nogloss>Beeps<\term> \       Causes Mailer to beep the specified number of times.
\ <term nogloss>Flashes<\term> \     Causes the icon or the Header window to             
                flash, depending on whether Mailer is closed to an icon
                or open.
\ <term nogloss>Sound File<\term> \  Causes Mailer to play the audio file specified in the text
                field as soon as new mail arrives.
<\lablist>
<\list>
<p>Clicking the Select button displays a File Selection dialog box in which
you can specify the sound file to be included in this field.

