Use the Rules Editor dialog box to create or modify your rules for
message filing.
 
<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=Mailer-Rules-Editor>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;
 
<term nogloss>Rule name<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Shows the name of the rule that contains the criteria that
you specify in this dialog box.  By default, the rule is on.
To turn it off, select the Off button.
<\list>
 
<term nogloss>Skip remaining rules if message matches this rule<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>With this option on, Mailer files a message <emph>only<\emph>
in the first mailbox in the Rules scrolling list in the Filing and
Notification Options dialog box that matches the rule and not
in other mailboxes, even if the other rules match.
 
<p>If you select this option, a good strategy is to place the more
specific rules at the beginning of the Rules scrolling list.  For
example, say you have the following rules:
 
<p>Rule 1 with the criteria <computer>From: writer@Eng<\computer> and
<computer>Subject: Status Report<\computer>, and Store message to:
<computer>writer-status<\computer> mailbox
 
<p>Rule 2 with the criteria <computer>From: writer@Eng<\computer>
and Store message to: <computer>writer-mail<\computer> mailbox

<p>Rule 1 is more restrictive than Rule 2 because it requires both
a specific sender and a specific subject, so it is placed first.
<\list>
 
<term nogloss>If message meets these criteria:<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Shows the criteria for the rule in one or more of these fields: To,
Cc, To or Cc, From, and Subject.  Except for the Subject field, a comma
or space in a field indicates <quote>or.<\quote>
<p>In the case of entries in multiple fields, an incoming message must
match the criteria in <emph>all<\emph> of these fields before Mailer will file
it away.
<\list>
 
<term nogloss>Then do this:<\term><newline>
<term nogloss>Store message to:<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Indicates the full path name of the mailbox to which messages
are to be filed.
<\list>
 
<term nogloss>Select Mailbox<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Opens a File Selection dialog box where you can specify the
full path name for the mailbox where messages are to be filed.
<\list>
 
<lablist>
\ Add \ Adds the rule to the Rules scrolling list in the <xref NotificationOptions>.
 
\ Change \ Changes the fields in this dialog box according to the edits
you have made.
 
\ Reset \ Resets the fields to their previous values.
<\lablist>
 
<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref NotificationOptions>
<\list>
-->
 

