	<idx>Move Down, in Toolbar Options dialog box<sort>move down, in toolbar 
options dialog box<\idx>

<p>Choose Toolbar from the Options menu to configure the appearance of the 
buttons in the Toolbar (located immediately below the Message Header 
List).  You can display the Toolbar buttons either as icons or with text.

<p>If the buttons are displayed as icons, as soon as you place
the cursor over an icon, a message is displayed below the Toolbar that 
tells you the command that the icon represents.

<p>The top pane shows the way the Toolbar is currently configured.  The
default display is icons for: Delete; Next; Previous; Reply, Include Message; 
Forward; New Message; and Print. 

<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=Mailer-Toolbar>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;

<term nogloss>Show Buttons As<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Determines whether the Toolbar buttons are displayed
as icons or with text (the default).
<\list>

<term nogloss>Commands<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Lists the buttons you can choose to be displayed in the Toolbar, 
either as icons or with text.
<\list>

<lablist>
\ Add \ Adds a selected command in the Commands list to the Toolbar list.

\ Remove \ Deletes a selected command in the Toolbar list.
<\lablist>

<term nogloss>Toolbar<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Lists the commands that you have chosen to be displayed in the 
Toolbar.
<\list>

<lablist>
\ Move Up \ Moves a selected command in the Toolbar toward the beginning of 
the list.

\ Move Down \ Moves a selected command in the Toolbar toward the end of the list.
<\lablist>

