<\list>
-->

<term nogloss>Vacation<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item>When Vacation is set On, Mailer sends a message that contains the text 
in the Subject and Message fields of this dialog box to each sender
of incoming mail messages.  
<p>Setting Vacation Off deactivates the vacation notifier.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Start Date<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item>The default is today's date.  Mailer starts sending the vacation
message starting at 12:01 a.m. of this date.
<\list>

<term nogloss>End Date<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item>Mailer stops sending the vacation message at 12:01 a.m. of 
this date. 
<\list>

<note>If the start and end dates are the same, then the vacation notifier 
ends at midnight of the End Date.<\note>

<term nogloss>Interval Between Replies To Repeat Senders<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item>The default setting is for the same sender to receive your 
vacation message once only in a seven-day period.  You can increase or 
decrease this default interval.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Subject<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item>Type the topic of the vacation notice.  The default is: <quote>
Out of the office.<\quote>
<\list>

<term nogloss>Message<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item>Type the body of the vacation notice (for example, <quote>Your mail 
regarding <computer>$SUBJECT<\computer> will be read when I return.<\quote>).
<computer>$SUBJECT<\computer> is a variable that is replaced by the 
subject of the message sent to you.
<\list>

