<s1 id=FindAMessage>Mailer Search Dialog Box
<location id=dtmailViewmainWindowMessageFind>&empty;<\location>
	<idx>Search dialog box, reference<sort>search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Search Type, in Search dialog box<sort>search type, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>To field, in Search dialog box<sort>to field, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>From field, in Search dialog box<sort>from field, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Subject field, in Search dialog box<sort>subject field, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Cc field, in Search dialog box<sort>cc field, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Entire Message field, in Search dialog box<sort>entire message field, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Headers, in Search dialog box<sort>headers, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Dates, in Search dialog box<sort>dates, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>States, in Search dialog box<sort>states, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Operators, in Search dialog box<sort>operators, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Search Down, in Search dialog box<sort>search down, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Search Up, in Search dialog box<sort>search up, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Save As View, in Search dialog box<sort>save as view, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Show Views, in Search dialog box<sort>show views, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Select All, in Search dialog box<sort>select all, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Clear, in Search dialog box<sort>clear, in search dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Cancel, in Search dialog box<sort>close, in search dialog box<\idx>

<p>Choosing Search from the Message menu opens the Search dialog box.

<p>In this dialog box, you can search for mail messages that match the 
search criteria that you define.  The more search criteria you specify, 
the more specific the match.

<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=Mailer-Search>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;

<lablist width=2in>
\ <term nogloss>Search Type<\term> \   

<list bullet tight>
<item><term nogloss>Basic<\term>: The dialog box that shows the To, From, 
Subject, Cc, and Entire Message fields, as well as the search buttons
<item><term nogloss>Advanced<\term>: The dialog box that shows the keyword 
menus (<link hyperlink=dtmailHeadersMenuInSearchDialogBox>Headers<\link>, 
<link hyperlink=dtmailDatesMenuInSearchDialogBox>Dates<\link>, <link hyperlink=dtmailStatesMenuInSearchDialogBox>States<\link>, and <link hyperlink=dtmailOperatorsMenuInSearchDialogBox>Operators<\link>), the text of the script, 
and the search buttons
<\list>

\ <term nogloss>To<\term> \		Searches by recipient.

\ <term nogloss>From<\term> \	Searches by sender.

\ <term nogloss>Subject<\term> \	Searches by subject keyword.

\ <term nogloss>Cc<\term> \		Searches by carbon-copy recipient.

\ <term nogloss>Entire Message<\term> \		Searches for the sequence of 
       characters that you type in the text field, <emph>inclusive<\emph> 
       of the headers.
<\lablist>

<note>These fields are <emph>not<\emph> case-sensitive.<\note>

<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=Mailer-Search-Adv>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;

<p>Here are the keywords you can use in search scripts.  Those you can
type manually but are not available through the menus are marked with an
asterisk (*).

<location id=dtmailHeadersMenuInSearchDialogBox>&empty;<\location>
<lablist>
\ <term nogloss>Headers<\term> \
\ TO \
\ FROM \
\ SUBJECT \ 
\ CC \
\ TEXT \ A keyword that pertains to the entire message, including headers
         and attachments
\ BCC \
\ HEADER* \ A keyword to use according to the syntax: <computer>header<\computer> <var>HeaderName<\var> <var>HeaderValue<\var>, such as <computer>header x-sun-charset us-ascii<\computer>
\ BODY* \ A keyword that applies to the message text and the text 
          attachments, but not the headers
<location id=dtmailDatesMenuInSearchDialogBox>&empty;<\location>
\ <term nogloss>Dates<\term> \ 
\ BEFORE \ 
\ SINCE \ 
\ ON \ 
\ DURING \ 
\ SENTSINCE* \  
\ SENTBEFORE* \  
\ SENTON* \  
\ TODAY \  An argument for the keywords that are associated with dates, such 
           as <computer>before<\computer>
\ YESTERDAY \  Same as above
\ LASTWEEK \   Same as above 
\ THISMONTH \  Same as above 
\ LASTMONTH \  Same as above 
\ JANUARY .. DECEMBER* \    
\ SUNDAY .. SATURDAY* \    
<location id=dtmailStatesMenuInSearchDialogBox>&empty;<\location>
\ <term nogloss>States<\term> \ 
\ READ \ 
\ UNREAD \ 
\ NEW* \ 
\ OLD* \ 
\ DELETED* \  A keyword for messages that you have deleted, but not permanently 
\ UNDELETED* \ 
\ RECENT* \ 
\ FLAGGED* \ 
\ UNFLAGGED* \ 
\ ANSWERED* \ 
\ UNANSWERED* \ 
\ KEYWORD* \ 
\ UNKEYWORD* \ 
\ DRAFT* \ 
\ UNDRAFT* \ 
\ ALL* \      A keyword that denotes all the messages in the mailbox
\ LARGER* \   A keyword that requires two arguments, such as <computer>smaller 300<\computer>, the numeric denoting bytes 
\ SMALLER* \    Same as above 
<location id=dtmailOperatorsMenuInSearchDialogBox>&empty;<\location>
\ <term nogloss>Operators<\term> \ 
\ AND \ 
\ OR \ 
\ ~ (not)  \ A symbol that represents the logical <computer>not<\computer> operator.  Place it in front of the search keyword, for example, <computer>~ text "good morning"<\computer>. 
\ ( \ A symbol that denotes the beginning of an expression 
\ ) \ A symbol that denotes the end of an expression 
<\lablist>

<note>The date format is dd-mmm-yyyy (for example, <computer>02-Apr-1996<\computer>).<\note>

<p>The following parameters set the scope of the search and close the Search 
dialog box.

<lablist width=2in>
\ Search Down \	 Searches for the next message in your mailbox that 
       matches the criteria, starting at the currently selected message.  
       If no match is found from there to the end of your mailbox, the 
       search wraps to the beginning of your mailbox.

<p>Once Mailer finds a match, it highlights the header of the message
that contains the match.

\ Search Up \  Searches for the next message in your mailbox that matches 
       the criteria, starting at the currently selected message toward the
       beginning of your mailbox.  If no match is found from there to the
       beginning of your mailbox, the search wraps to the end of 
       your mailbox.

\ Save As View \	Displays the Save As View dialog box, where you 
            specify a view name for the search criteria that you have 
            defined (for example, Docs).	

\ Show Views \   Displays the <xref DTMAILHELPVIEWS> where you can create, 
            edit, delete, or update views.

\ Select All \		Finds and selects all messages that match the filled-in
                    fields.

\ Clear \   Removes the text in the search fields and the advanced script 
            text area if a script is being displayed.

\ Cancel \  Cancels the Search operation and closes the dialog box.
<\lablist>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref FindingMessagesTA>
<item> <xref DTMAILHELPVIEWS>
<\list>

<s1 id=DTMAILHELPVIEWS>Mailer Views Dialog Box
	<idx>Views dialog box, reference<sort>views dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Default Views, Views Dialog Box<sort>default views, views dialog box<\idx>
