<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=Mailer-Views>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;

<p>Choosing Show Views from the Mailbox menu or clicking Show Views in the
Search dialog box opens the Views dialog box.

<p>In this dialog box, you can create, edit, delete, load, or update views
for your search criteria for mail messages. 

<term nogloss>Default Views<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Message statistics for the entire mailbox (All) and messages 
that you have not yet read (New)
<\list>

<term nogloss>Custom Views<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>The views that you defined in the Search dialog box, with their 
message statistics under New and Total
<\list>

<!--
<term nogloss>Current View<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>The name of the view that is being displayed in the main window
<\list>
-->

<term nogloss>Up Arrow<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Moves a selected view toward the top of the Customs Views list.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Down Arrow<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Moves a selected view toward the bottom of the Customs Views list.
<\list>

<lablist>
\ New \  Displays the Search dialog box, where you can define search 
         criteria and create views.

\ Edit \ Displays the Search dialog box with the search criteria that you 
         defined for the selected view.

\ Delete \ Deletes the selected view.
 
\ Load \ Displays the messages that match the criteria for the selected 
         view in the main window.

\ Update \ Revises and displays the New and Total statistics for all the views.
 
\ Close \ Dismisses the Views dialog box.
<\lablist>

