<s1 id=DTMAILHELPFILESELECTIONBOX>File Selection Dialog Box

	<idx>file selection dialog box<\idx>

When you perform certain functions, like Open Mailbox or Save, the File 
Selection dialog box is a standard way to access your file system.

<newline>&empty;
<figure nonumber entity=Mailer-File-Selection-Box>
<\figure>
<newline>&empty;

<note>The title bar and the buttons of the dialog box vary, depending on 
the operation you wish to perform.<\note>

<term nogloss>Local or IMAP Server<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item>Select to specify the mail server type.  If you select IMAP
Server, type its name in the text field.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Enter path or folder name<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item>The path and the folder name for the item. 
This location can be anywhere in your file system. 
If folders are selected in the Folders field, the path appears here.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Filter<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Optional: An asterisk (*) shows all files. You can enter wildcard 
characters to display only those files that match an extension. 
For example, <computer>*.tif<\computer> lists only those files with a 
<computer>.tif<\computer> extension.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Folders<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item>A list of the folders in the current directory.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Files<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item>A list of the files within the current folder.
<\list>

<!--
<term nogloss>Show hidden folders and files<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Optional: Toggles whether to list certain files 
that are usually hidden from view, such as . (dot) files. 
<\list>
-->

<term nogloss>Enter file name<\term> 
<list plain tight>
<item>Type the name of the file or select it from the list.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Open Mailbox<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Performs the specified action and dismisses the dialog box.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Update<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Displays a new list of files after changing the filter key or 
changing to a new folder.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Cancel<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Halts the operation without applying the changes.
<\list>

<term nogloss>Help<\term>
<list plain tight>
<item>Opens the help viewer that displays information about this dialog box.
<\list>

